cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a language that is consistent when interpreted as a logic and presents a new technique for normalization in the logical fragment.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper presents designs for practical dependently typed languages and discusses a language with general recursion.
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with dependently typed languages and mentions passing information between logical and programmatic fragments.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses a language design and metatheory.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with the formal properties of a language.
